[4] Suspected, monitored, quarantined, prevention

31 Dec 2014 (Iraqi News) 2 Ebola cases "confirmed" [registered] in Mosul, Iraq
http://www.iraqinews.com/features/urgent-two-ebola-cases-confirmed-mosul/

The Iraqi official newspaper 'Al-Sabah' said in today's [Wed 31 Dec 2014] issue: "Many diseases and epidemics have spread among residents of the city of Mosul," and added: "2 Ebola and 26 HIV AIDS cases were registered." The newspaper quoted medical sources in the city: "These diseases moved to Nineveh ... from different countries, especially Africa." On 23 Nov 2014, the Parliamentary Committee of Health and Environment [expressed concern about] the entry of Ebola into Iraq by the Islamic State (IS) while confirming that the Commission had taken the necessary measures to prevent the entry and spread of this disease in the country.

